HEADWORD: hawsepipe
<hw>hawse"pipe`</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>a hole in the bow of a ship, through which the anchor rope or cable
passes.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hawse, hawsepipe.</syn>⟦br⟧
